                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-114-off595 t18220703-114-crimeloc598"></join>. On the 5th of June, about eleven o'clock, I left my wife in the shop. I returned about one o'clock, and found the prisoner in charge with this bacon - which I knew by having cut it myself just before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-114-person976">
                  WILLIAM 
                  ROBERTSON
               <interp inst="t18220703-114-person976" type="surname" value="ROBERTSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-114-person976" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-114-person976" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shoe-maker, and live opposite James's. I was at my door, and saw Farrell go into James's house, and come out in a minute with three pieces of bacon. Thomas stood at the door. I followed, and took both. I saw him give it to Thomas.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>THOMAS'S Defence. I was a stranger to Farrell - he asked me to hold the bacon.</p>
